      "Unnamed: 5": NaN,
      "Change or optimization": "Starting Point: Sales Orders drive the process, with items linked to BOMs \nthat include approximate weights for raw material planning.\nManufacturing Plan: Aggregates items from Sales Orders for planning.\nParent Manufacturing Order (PMO): Created one per unit of quantity (e.g., 221 qty = 221 PMOs)\n to enable granular tracking of each individual item through the process.\nManufacturing Operations: Linked to each PMO, with raw materials transferred to department-specific warehouses.\nTransaction Tracking:\nDepartment IR and Employee IR: Record issues/receives within departments and between employees.\nStock Movement Log: A ledger-style doctype for + (inward) and - (outward) movements,\n tracking custody at operation, department, and employee levels.\n\nStock Handling: Physical stock movements (inbound/outbound) use standard Stock Entries, but internal transactions \nuse the custom log to avoid Stock Entry's validation overhead and slowness.\n",
